---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "April 24, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | landrycmd"
  description="Privacy policy for landrycmd and its products."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how landrycmd (EIN 41-4998290) and its
      operator Brady Landry (collectively, "we," "us," or "landrycmd")
      collect, use, and disclose information in connection with our website
      at <a href="https://landrycmd.com">landrycmd.com</a> and our products
      (including Jarvis Quant, Jarvis, and PeptideTracker).
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on the product, we may collect: (a) account information you
      provide when signing up, such as email address and display name; (b)
      usage data you generate while using the product, such as entries you
      log, configurations you create, and interactions with the service;
      (c) device and browser information automatically logged by standard
      web analytics and error reporting (IP address, user agent, referring
      URL, timestamps); (d) content of messages sent to us for support.
    </p>

    <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use collected information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Operate, maintain, and improve our products and services</li>
      <li>Respond to your support requests and communicate with you</li>
      <li>
        Send transactional communications related to your account or use of
        a product (e.g., verification codes, receipts, service alerts)
      </li>
      <li>Detect, prevent, and address technical or security issues</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. SMS / messaging communications</h2>
    <p>
      If you opt in to receive SMS or other messages from us (for example,
      transactional alerts from a landrycmd product), you agree to receive
      messages at the phone number you provide. Message frequency varies.
      Standard message and data rates may apply. You can opt out at any
      time by replying <code>STOP</code> to any message; reply
      <code>HELP</code> for assistance. We do not share phone numbers or
      message content with third parties for marketing purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Sharing and disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell personal information. We share information only with:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Service providers (hosting, analytics, error reporting, payment
        processing, messaging carriers) who process data on our behalf
        under contract
      </li>
      <li>
        Authorities when required by law, legal process, or to protect
        rights and safety
      </li>
      <li>
        A successor entity in connection with a merger, acquisition, or
        sale of assets
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain account and usage information for as long as your account
      is active or as needed to provide the service, and for a reasonable
      period thereafter to comply with legal obligations, resolve
      disputes, and enforce agreements. Deletion requests can be sent to
      the email below.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your choices and rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal
      information we hold about you by contacting
      <a href="mailto:support@landrycmd.com">support@landrycmd.com</a>.
      Residents of certain jurisdictions (including California and the
      European Economic Area) may have additional rights under applicable
      law; we will honor those rights to the extent required.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use industry-standard administrative, technical, and physical
      safeguards to protect information. No method of transmission or
      storage is completely secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children</h2>
    <p>
      Our products are not directed to children under 13, and we do not
      knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If
      you believe we have collected information from a child under 13,
      please contact us and we will delete it.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we
      will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
      Continued use of our products after changes constitutes acceptance of
      the revised policy.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or requests: <a href="mailto:support@landrycmd.com"
        >support@landrycmd.com</a
      >. Mailing address provided upon request.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
